bestBHT.bht: Bring of the fish ye have now caught—observe the double supply thus provided—His and theirs. Emphasizing the fish as food, the disciples had caught them by Christ's direction, yet He courteously says they have caught them. The meal consists of materials provided by the combined action of Jesus and His disciples, with the disciples gaining a more perfect knowledge of the miracle. This is not only about physical fish but also symbolic of bringing souls to Christ through the ministry of the word.

The disciples were instructed to bring of the fish they had caught, signifying the double supply provided - His and theirs. Although they had caught the fish by Christ's direction, He courteously acknowledged their efforts. The meal consisted of materials provided by both Jesus and His disciples, allowing them to gain a deeper understanding of the miracle. This event not only emphasized the physical food but also served as a symbol of bringing souls to Christ through the ministry of the word.

The disciples were instructed to bring of the fish they had now caught, acknowledging the double supply provided - both from Jesus and themselves. While they had caught the fish by Christ's direction, He graciously credited them for their efforts. This moment showcased the provision of food through the combined action of Jesus and His disciples, allowing them to witness and understand the miracle in a more profound way. Moreover, this event symbolizes the importance of bringing souls to Christ through the ministry of the word.
